<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,406,918,944]" box="[189,406,918,944]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,406,918,944]" fontSize="11" level="4" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,406,918,944]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Short description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,965,1133]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Epiphytic; long-creeping filiform rhizomes, rootless and densely covered by dense black trichomes, bearing widely separated pending fronds; fronds subsessile to well stipitate, up to 1.5 cm long (in Comoros, longer in Continental Africa), ovate or obovate to elliptic, entire to lobed, with palmate venation, and false veins parallel to true veins in addition to a submarginal false vein; sori few, epitactic, campanulate with a slightly dilated mouth.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
